nodes.name: Colorado Privacy Act
nodes.description: The CPA is Colorado's comprehensive consumer privacy law that protects the privacy rights of Colorado residents, establishes controller and processor obligations, and grants enforcement authority to the Colorado Attorney General and District Attorneys.

nodes.summary: Establishes short title as Colorado Privacy Act
nodes.name: Short Title

nodes.key_provisions: Consumer privacy protection; Business certainty; Harmonization with other state laws
nodes.name: Legislative Declaration

nodes.summary: Defines key terms including PersonalData SensitiveData Sale Controller Processor Consumer
nodes.key_provisions: 27 definitions including: Consent; Consumer; Controller; DeidentifiedData; PersonalData; Processing; Processor; Profiling; Sale; SensitiveData; TargetedAdvertising; ThirdParty; UniversalOptOutMechanism
nodes.name: Definitions

nodes.summary: Defines thresholds: 100000+ consumers OR 25000+ with revenue from sale
nodes.key_provisions: 100000+ consumers threshold; 25000+ consumers + revenue threshold; Exclusions for small businesses; HIPAA GLBA FCRA exclusions
nodes.name: Applicability

nodes.summary: Controller and processor obligations including data processing agreements
nodes.key_provisions: Controller duties: security; data minimization; purpose limitation; Processor duties: assist controller; data processing agreement requirements
nodes.name: Duties of Controllers and Processors

nodes.summary: Establishes 5 consumer rights: Access Correct Delete Portability OptOut
nodes.key_provisions: Right to access; Right to correct; Right to delete; Right to portability; Right to opt out of: targeted advertising sale profiling; 45-day response deadline; Appeal process; AG notification if denied
nodes.name: Consumer Personal Data Rights

nodes.summary: Exemptions and exclusions from CPA coverage
nodes.key_provisions: Processing for internal research; De-identified data processing; Certain employment contexts; Federal law compliance
nodes.name: Activities Not Covered

nodes.summary: Opt-in consent requirement; minimization; CRITICAL: § 6-1-1308(4) secondary use prohibition
nodes.key_provisions: Opt-in consent for sensitive data; Data minimization for sensitive data; Purpose limitation for sensitive data; § 6-1-1308(4): No secondary use without new consent
nodes.name: Duties Regarding Sensitive Personal Data

nodes.summary: DPA requirements for high-risk processing; AG disclosure obligation within 30 days
nodes.key_provisions: DPA required for: targeted advertising; sale; profiling with legal effects; sensitive data processing; DPA must weigh benefits vs risks; Must disclose to AG within 30 days of request
nodes.name: Data Protection Assessments

nodes.key_provisions: Deletion methods; Retention exceptions; Third-party notification
nodes.name: Deletion of Personal Data

nodes.summary: Attorney General enforcement authority; civil penalties; cure period sunset
nodes.key_provisions: Exclusive enforcement by AG and District Attorneys; Civil penalties up to $20000/violation; Discretionary cure period (mandatory cure period ended 2025-01-01); Injunctive relief; No private right of action
nodes.name: Enforcement

nodes.summary: Authorizes Attorney General to issue CPA Rules
nodes.key_provisions: AG authority to promulgate rules implementing CPA; CPA Rules (4 CCR 904-3) issued pursuant to this section
nodes.name: Rulemaking

nodes.summary: Federal law preemption; HIPAA GLBA FCRA exclusions
nodes.key_provisions: HIPAA covered entities/business associates; GLBA institutions; FCRA consumer reporting agencies; Non-profit organizations; Higher education institutions (in certain contexts)
nodes.name: Exclusions
Universal Opt-Out Mechanism
nodes.requirement: Controllers must recognize universal opt-out mechanisms (UOOMs) such as Global Privacy Control (GPC) browser signals as valid opt-out requests for targeted advertising and sales of personal data

nodes.name: Privacy Notice Requirements
nodes.requirement: Controllers must provide clear and conspicuous privacy notice covering: categories of personal data collected; purposes of collection; categories of personal data shared or sold; categories of third parties; consumer rights including opt-out mechanisms

nodes.name: Consent Requirements
nodes.requirement: Consent must be: clear affirmative act; freely given; specific; informed; unambiguous. Prohibited consent practices: dark patterns; pre-checked boxes; acceptance of general terms only; hovering muting or pausing; consent bundled with acceptance of terms as precondition of service

nodes.name: Secondary Use Restrictions
nodes.requirement: Controllers must obtain new consent if processing purpose materially changes from originally disclosed purpose (implements § 6-1-1308(4) secondary use prohibition)

nodes.text: Information that is linked or reasonably linkable to an identified or identifiable individual
nodes.cross_references: Excludes de-identified data per § 6-1-1303(11); Excludes publicly available information; Excludes employee/B2B data in certain contexts

nodes.text: Personal data revealing: racial or ethnic origin; religious beliefs; mental or physical health condition or diagnosis; sex life or sexual orientation; citizenship or citizenship status; genetic or biometric data processed for purpose of uniquely identifying individual; or personal data from known child
nodes.cross_references: Requires opt-in consent per § 6-1-1308(1); Subject to data minimization per § 6-1-1308(3); Subject to secondary use prohibition per § 6-1-1308(4)

nodes.text: Exchange of personal data for monetary consideration OR OTHER VALUABLE CONSIDERATION by controller to third party
nodes.cross_references: Broader than VCDPA (includes non-monetary value like CCPA); Excludes certain disclosures to processors or for specific purposes; Subject to opt-out right per § 6-1-1306(1)(d)(II)

nodes.text: Person that alone or jointly with others determines the purposes and means of processing personal data
nodes.cross_references: Must meet applicability thresholds per § 6-1-1304; Owes duties per § 6-1-1305 and § 6-1-1308

nodes.text: Person that processes personal data on behalf of controller
nodes.cross_references: Bound by data processing agreement per § 6-1-1305(2); Must assist controller with consumer rights requests; Must assist with DPAs

nodes.text: Individual who is a Colorado resident acting only in an individual or household context
nodes.cross_references: Excludes individuals acting in commercial or employment context; Has rights under § 6-1-1306

nodes.text: Any operation or set of operations performed on personal data including: collection; use; storage; disclosure; analysis; deletion; modification; sharing
nodes.cross_references: Broad definition covers all data activities; Subject to controller duties

nodes.text: Data that cannot reasonably be used to infer information about or otherwise be linked to an identified or identifiable individual or device
nodes.cross_references: Exempt from CPA if technical and organizational measures applied; Controller must commit to not re-identify; Cannot combine with other information to identify

nodes.text: Person other than: consumer; controller; processor; or affiliate of controller or processor
nodes.cross_references: Recipients in data sales or sharing; Controller liable for third-party misuse

nodes.text: Displaying advertisements to consumer based on personal data obtained from consumer's activity across non-affiliated websites applications or online services
nodes.cross_references: Subject to opt-out right per § 6-1-1306(1)(d)(I); Requires DPA per § 6-1-1309

nodes.text: Automated processing of personal data to evaluate analyze or predict personal aspects concerning economic situation health preferences interests reliability behavior location or movements
nodes.cross_references: Subject to opt-out right if produces legal or similarly significant effects per § 6-1-1306(1)(d)(III); Requires DPA per § 6-1-1309

nodes.text: Clear affirmative act signifying freely given specific informed and unambiguous agreement to process personal data
nodes.cross_references: Required for sensitive data per § 6-1-1308(1); Must meet Rule 7.03 standards; Cannot use dark patterns; Must be revocable

nodes.text: Mechanism that communicates or signals consumer's choice to opt out of processing personal data for purposes of targeted advertising or sale
nodes.cross_references: Controllers must honor by 2024-07-01 per Rule 5.01; Examples: Global Privacy Control (GPC); Must be single request; No account required

nodes.right_description: Consumer may confirm whether controller is processing their personal data and access such personal data in a portable and readily usable format.
nodes.name: Right to Access

nodes.right_description: Consumer may correct inaccuracies in their personal data taking into account the nature and purposes of processing.
nodes.name: Right to Correct

nodes.right_description: Consumer may delete personal data provided by or obtained about the consumer subject to exceptions for legal obligations, public health, and abuse detection.
nodes.name: Right to Delete

nodes.right_description: Consumer may obtain a copy of personal data previously provided to controller in a portable and to the extent technically feasible readily usable format that allows transmission to another entity.
nodes.name: Right to Data Portability

nodes.right_description: Consumer may opt out of: (I) targeted advertising; (II) sale of personal data; (III) profiling in furtherance of decisions that produce legal or similarly significant effects. UOOM signals must be honored immediately.
nodes.response_deadline_days: Immediate for UOOM; 45 for direct requests
nodes.name: Right to Opt Out

nodes.response_timeframe: Immediate if via UOOM; 45 days if direct request
nodes.description: Consumer may opt out of processing of personal data for purposes of targeted advertising; precision marketing; behavioral advertising; profiling for advertising purposes

nodes.response_timeframe: Immediate if via UOOM; 45 days if direct request
nodes.description: Consumer may opt out of sale of personal data for monetary or other valuable consideration; includes direct sales and disclosure for valuable consideration; sharing data for compensation
nodes.type: Opt Out of Sale of Personal Data

nodes.response_timeframe: Immediate if via UOOM; 45 days if direct request
nodes.description: Consumer may opt out of profiling in furtherance of decisions that produce legal or similarly significant effects concerning the consumer; automated decision-making; credit decisions; employment decisions
nodes.type: Opt Out of Profiling with Legal Effects

nodes.penalty_for_violation: Civil penalty up to $20000 per violation
nodes.name: Duty of Data Minimization
nodes.description: Controller shall limit collection of personal data to what is adequate, relevant, and reasonably necessary in relation to the purposes for which data is processed.

nodes.penalty_for_violation: Civil penalty up to $20000 per violation
nodes.name: Duty to Avoid Secondary Use
nodes.description: Controller shall not process personal data for purposes that are not reasonably necessary to, or compatible with, the disclosed purposes for which such personal data is processed, unless the controller obtains the consumer's consent.

nodes.penalty_for_violation: Civil penalty up to $20000 per violation
nodes.name: Duty to Respond to Rights Requests
nodes.description: Controller shall respond to consumer rights requests within 45 days (extendable by 45 days with notice); provide an appeal process if request is denied; inform consumer of right to contact Attorney General if appeal is denied.

nodes.penalty_for_violation: Civil penalty up to $20000 per violation
nodes.name: Duty to Honor Universal Opt-Out
nodes.description: Controller shall honor universal opt-out mechanism signals (such as Global Privacy Control) as valid opt-out requests for targeted advertising and sales of personal data.

nodes.penalty_for_violation: Civil penalty up to $20000 per violation
nodes.name: Duty to Provide Privacy Notice
nodes.description: Controller shall provide clear and conspicuous privacy notice disclosing: categories of personal data collected; purposes of processing; whether data is shared or sold; consumer rights; and available opt-out mechanisms.

nodes.penalty_for_violation: Civil penalty up to $20000 per violation
nodes.name: Duty to Obtain Valid Consent
nodes.description: Controller shall obtain clear, affirmative, freely-given, specific, informed, and unambiguous consent for processing sensitive personal data; shall not use dark patterns or prohibited consent practices.

nodes.name: Colorado Attorney General
nodes.powers: Issue CPA Rules per § 6-1-1312; Bring civil enforcement actions; Seek civil penalties up to $20000 per violation; Issue injunctions; Request Data Protection Assessments from controllers within 30 days; Grant discretionary cure periods (mandatory cure period ended 2025-01-01)

nodes.contact: County District Attorney offices across Colorado
nodes.name: District Attorneys
nodes.powers: Bring civil enforcement actions; Seek civil penalties up to $20000 per violation (concurrent authority with Attorney General)

nodes.penalty_framework: Colorado Consumer Protection Act penalty structure
nodes.legal_citation: § 6-1-1311 (enforced via C.R.S. § 6-1-112 Colorado Consumer Protection Act)

nodes.name: 100K Consumer Volume Threshold
nodes.applicability_test: Controller that, during a calendar year, controls or processes personal data of 100,000 or more consumers

nodes.name: 25K Consumer + Revenue Threshold
nodes.type: Annual Consumer Data Volume + Revenue from Sale
nodes.applicability_test: Controller that, during a calendar year: (a) controls or processes personal data of 25,000 or more consumers; AND (b) derives revenue or receives a discount on the price of goods or services from the sale of personal data
nodes.revenue_condition: Derives revenue or receives discount from sale of personal data

nodes.name: Controller-Processor Data Processing Agreement
nodes.mandatory_terms: Instructions: Controller's instructions for processing; Nature and Purpose: Nature purpose and duration of processing; Data Types: Type of personal data and categories of data subjects; Obligations: Controller's and processor's obligations and rights; Return/Deletion: Procedures for return or deletion of personal data upon completion of services or termination of agreement; Confidentiality: Confidentiality commitments of persons authorized to process personal data; Security: Appropriate technical and organizational security measures; Assistance: Processor assistance with controller's obligations to respond to consumer rights requests; DPA Support: Processor assistance with controller's Data Protection Assessment obligations; Audits: Controller's right to take reasonable steps to ensure processor is meeting obligations including right to audit; Subprocessors: Subcontractor requirements binding subcontractors to same obligations as processor

nodes.applicable_activities: Targeted Advertising; Sale of Personal Data; Profiling with legal or similarly significant effects
nodes.technical_standard: GPC header detection (Sec-GPC: 1 in HTTP request header)
nodes.examples: Global Privacy Control (GPC); Browser opt-out signals; User-agent-based signals
nodes.name: Universal Opt-Out Mechanism
De-Identified Data
nodes.organizational_requirements: Public commitment not to attempt to re-identify data; Contractual obligations on data recipients not to re-identify; Policies and procedures to maintain de-identified status
nodes.definition: Data that cannot reasonably be used to infer information about or otherwise be linked to an identified or identifiable individual or device linked to such individual
nodes.technical_requirements: Data rendered non-identifiable using appropriate technical measures; Reasonable assurance data cannot be re-identified through technical means; Cannot combine with other information to identify individual or device

nodes.relationships: Receives personal data via Sale from controller; Receives personal data via sharing/disclosure from controller; Not directly bound by consumer's original consent to controller; May become controller in own right for data received
nodes.controller_liability: Controller remains liable for third-party misuse if controller violates CPA in transfer; Controller must conduct DPA before sale to third party
nodes.name: Third Party
nodes.obligations: Limited direct CPA obligations; Not subject to controller duties unless acting as controller for received data
nodes.definition: Person other than: (a) consumer; (b) controller; (c) processor; or (d) affiliate of controller or processor

nodes.immediate_actions_taken: Systems isolated; Ransom negotiated; Data restored
nodes.data_types_compromised: Email; Names; Payment info; Medical records

nodes.immediate_actions_taken: Notified consumer; File recovered; Enhanced backups
nodes.lessons_learned: Improved access controls; Better recovery procedures

nodes.risks_identified: Privacy invasion; Profiling risks; Minor protection

nodes.risk_description: Sale of sensitive data; Inadequate safeguards
Health data processing; Parental consent required
nodes.risk_mitigation_measures: Encryption; Access controls; Audit trails; Consent

nodes.security_requirements: Encryption at rest and in transit; Access controls with audit logging; Role-based access; Data minimization required
nodes.name: Personal Data Revealing Racial or Ethnic Origin
nodes.description: Personal data that reveals or is used to infer a consumer's racial or ethnic origin
nodes.processing_restrictions: Requires opt-in consent; Purpose limitation strictly enforced; Cannot be used for discriminatory purposes

nodes.security_requirements: Encryption at rest and in transit; Access controls with audit logging; Need-to-know basis access only
nodes.name: Personal Data Revealing Religious Beliefs
nodes.description: Personal data that reveals or is used to infer a consumer's religious beliefs or affiliations
nodes.processing_restrictions: Requires opt-in consent; Cannot be used for discriminatory purposes or targeting; Purpose limitation strictly enforced

nodes.security_requirements: Encryption at rest and in transit; Access controls; Audit logging; HIPAA-compliant security measures where applicable
nodes.name: Personal Data Revealing Mental or Physical Health Diagnosis
nodes.description: Personal data revealing a consumer's mental or physical health diagnosis; treatment; or condition including pregnancy
nodes.processing_restrictions: Requires opt-in consent; HIPAA alignment recommended; Purpose limitation strictly enforced; Cannot be disclosed without authorization

nodes.security_requirements: Encryption with enhanced protection; Restricted access with audit logging; Segregated storage recommended
nodes.name: Personal Data Revealing Sex Life or Sexual Orientation
nodes.description: Personal data that reveals or is used to infer a consumer's sex life or sexual orientation
nodes.processing_restrictions: Requires opt-in consent; Cannot be used for discriminatory purposes; Enhanced protection required; Purpose limitation strictly enforced

nodes.security_requirements: Encryption at rest and in transit; Restricted access; Audit logging; Segregated storage; Legal review required for disclosures
nodes.name: Personal Data Revealing Citizenship or Immigration Status
nodes.description: Personal data that reveals or is used to infer a consumer's citizenship status or immigration status
nodes.processing_restrictions: Requires opt-in consent; Cannot be disclosed to immigration authorities without legal process; Enhanced protection required

nodes.security_requirements: Biometric-grade encryption; Restricted access with multi-factor authentication; Segregated storage; Tamper-evident audit logs; Annual security assessments
nodes.name: Genetic Data
nodes.description: Genetic data processed for the purpose of uniquely identifying an individual including DNA sequencing; genetic heritage information; hereditary disease markers
nodes.processing_restrictions: Requires opt-in consent; Cannot be disclosed without explicit authorization; GINA compliance required; State genetic privacy law alignment required; Enhanced purpose limitation

nodes.security_requirements: Biometric-grade encryption; Secure enclave storage; Multi-factor authentication; Role-based access; Tamper-evident audit logs
nodes.name: Biometric Data for Unique Identification
nodes.description: Biometric data processed for purpose of uniquely identifying a consumer including fingerprints; facial recognition templates; iris scans; voice prints; gait analysis
nodes.processing_restrictions: Requires opt-in consent; Must be deleted upon consumer request or when purpose ends; Cannot be sold; Enhanced security required; Illinois BIPA considerations

nodes.security_requirements: Encryption at rest and in transit; Access controls; Audit logging; Anonymization when aggregated
nodes.name: Precise Geolocation Data
nodes.description: Precise geolocation data derived from device tracking within 1750 feet radius revealing consumer's physical location or movements
nodes.processing_restrictions: Requires opt-in consent; Must clearly disclose tracking purposes; Can be used for navigation with consent; Enhanced deletion rights; Purpose limitation

nodes.security_requirements: Enhanced encryption; Restricted access; Parental oversight mechanisms; Audit logging; Age verification safeguards
nodes.name: Child Personal Data
nodes.description: Personal data processed with actual knowledge that the data are from a child under 13 years of age
nodes.processing_restrictions: Requires verifiable parental consent; COPPA compliance required; Enhanced deletion rights; Cannot be used for targeted advertising; Data minimization strictly required; Purpose limitation

nodes.security_requirements: Encryption at rest and in transit; Tokenization recommended; Multi-factor authentication; Segregated storage; Audit logging; PCI-DSS alignment where applicable
nodes.name: Social Security Numbers and Government IDs
nodes.description: Social Security numbers; driver's license numbers; state identification card numbers; passport numbers; or other government-issued identification numbers
nodes.processing_restrictions: Requires opt-in consent; Strict purpose limitation (identity verification; fraud prevention; legal compliance only); Enhanced retention limits; Deletion required when purpose ends
